CNCP v1 23463
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#9546: defineProps options object loses properties when using generics",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:30.817914+00:00",
  "text": "defineProps options object loses properties when using generics\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.3.7 & 3.4.alpha\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n<img width=\"443\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/vuejs/core/assets/4620458/71dad487-a49c-4c18-8fa1-05851ec62fd2\">\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<script setup lang=\"ts\" generic=\"T\">\r\nimport { PropType } from 'vue'\r\nconst props = defineProps({\r\n  a: Object as PropType<T>,\r\n\r\n  b: {\r\n    type: Object as PropType<T>\r\n  },\r\n\r\n  c: {\r\n    type: Object as PropType<T>,\r\n    required: true,\r\n  }\r\n})\r\n\r\nprops.a\r\nprops.b\r\nprops.c\r\n</script>\r\n```\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe props to be declared correctly\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nProperties are been excluded from props, unless they are required 🤔 \n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types",
    ":hammer: p3-minor-bug"
  ],
